1
00:00:34,036 --> 00:00:37,760
Interviewer: How did you feel as you left
the interrogation room for the cell?

2
00:00:37,785 --> 00:00:41,927
You can’t describe it. A prisoner is
being led to prison—what can he do?

3
00:00:42,178 --> 00:00:44,469
He can’t run away
or do anything else.

4
00:00:45,433 --> 00:00:48,610
If I had known it would
end with flogging and torture,

5
00:00:48,635 --> 00:00:50,641
I wouldn’t have gone
back to retrieve my ID card.

6
00:00:51,422 --> 00:00:55,329
Interviewer: Could you tell us about
the ISIS escort who was with you?

7
00:00:55,354 --> 00:00:59,105
I told him there was no
need for prison and flogging.

8
00:00:59,130 --> 00:01:00,511
I hadn’t committed a crime.

9
00:01:01,110 --> 00:01:02,933
He said, The judge is the
one who sentenced you,

10
00:01:02,958 --> 00:01:07,672
to spend a full day in prison
and be released the next day

11
00:01:08,271 --> 00:01:11,318
as a punishment because
you argued with the guards.

12
00:01:13,532 --> 00:01:15,537
Tomorrow they’ll flog
you and let you go.

13
00:01:16,839 --> 00:01:19,521
I stayed with the prisoners, and
the next day they called my name,

14
00:01:21,370 --> 00:01:22,282
and they flogged me.

15
00:01:22,850 --> 00:01:25,037
Interviewer: Did they tell you exactly
what time you’d be released the next day?

16
00:01:25,062 --> 00:01:28,658
Yes, and he said, This is a
punishment so you won’t repeat it.

17
00:01:29,361 --> 00:01:32,147
You’ll be jailed and
released the following day.

18
00:01:33,267 --> 00:01:35,559
They’ll flog you one hundred
lashes and let you out.

19
00:01:35,584 --> 00:01:37,798
The judge sentenced
me to one hundred lashes,

20
00:01:38,267 --> 00:01:39,439
and I argued with him.

21
00:01:58,658 --> 00:02:00,663
This place was full
of ISIS members.

22
00:02:07,068 --> 00:02:12,823
Interviewer: When you arrived here, in
this hall where people were also detained,

23
00:02:13,162 --> 00:02:14,907
was the door open?

24
00:02:14,932 --> 00:02:17,224
No, the door was closed.

25
00:02:18,058 --> 00:02:19,282
It wasn’t open; it was shut.

26
00:02:19,438 --> 00:02:23,891
There were also many people.

27
00:02:24,464 --> 00:02:26,834
There were a lot
of detainees inside.

28
00:02:29,959 --> 00:02:31,469
Interviewer: And you
couldn’t see anything?

29
00:02:31,494 --> 00:02:32,771
No, I couldn’t see.

30
00:02:35,480 --> 00:02:37,198
It was like a prison, too.

31
00:02:39,881 --> 00:02:41,209
But that detention
area is upstairs.

32
00:02:43,631 --> 00:02:44,855
Interviewer: Do you have
memories of the upstairs area?

33
00:02:44,881 --> 00:02:48,292
I do. When we
entered the prison,

34
00:02:48,493 --> 00:02:50,420
it was crowded with prisoners.

35
00:02:52,321 --> 00:02:54,483
It was packed, not just
one or two prisoners;

36
00:02:55,681 --> 00:02:57,530
there were many.

37
00:02:58,728 --> 00:03:00,108
Interviewer: Do
you see that corner?

38
00:03:09,821 --> 00:03:11,097
That corner.

39
00:03:12,139 --> 00:03:13,623
Interviewer: What
does it remind you of?

40
00:03:14,300 --> 00:03:16,149
When I left I
didn’t see it well.

41
00:03:20,212 --> 00:03:21,071
Interviewer: You
know nothing about it?

42
00:03:21,096 --> 00:03:24,457
I don’t know. I left right away.

43
00:03:27,073 --> 00:03:28,323
At the end of the liberation?

44
00:03:29,183 --> 00:03:32,620
They confiscated all the
satellite broadcast devices.

45
00:03:32,933 --> 00:03:35,120
They used to bring them to their
<i>Hisba</i> bases.

46
00:03:36,110 --> 00:03:40,042
Satellite receivers
and their accessories.

47
00:03:40,067 --> 00:03:42,308
They’d bring them and
store them with the <i>Hisba</i>.

48
00:03:43,141 --> 00:03:45,198
Interviewer: Did they come to
your house and confiscate anything?

49
00:03:45,223 --> 00:03:48,922
Yes, they came, took the
satellite receiver, and left.

50
00:03:50,094 --> 00:03:53,454
So we wouldn’t know what
was happening in the news

51
00:03:55,120 --> 00:03:57,776
Interviewer: And what about those who
don’t want to hand over the satellite dish?

52
00:03:57,985 --> 00:04:00,797
Whoever doesn’t want to hand over
the device, they take him and detain him

53
00:04:02,413 --> 00:04:05,304
And whoever they catch with a
satellite dish, they detain him too

54
00:04:06,267 --> 00:04:10,563
For example, someone who hands over one
satellite dish and hides another from them

55
00:04:10,588 --> 00:04:12,908
Then an informer’s
tip comes in about him

56
00:04:13,220 --> 00:04:17,335
Because there were informants
walking among the people

57
00:04:20,850 --> 00:04:24,757
I mean, the informants were
moving among the people

58
00:04:24,782 --> 00:04:27,335
And they find out who
owns a satellite dish

59
00:04:27,934 --> 00:04:30,668
They report on people

60
00:04:31,397 --> 00:04:33,481
I mean, there were
informants in Mosul

61
00:04:33,871 --> 00:04:35,798
They delivered the
information to ISIS

62
00:04:37,673 --> 00:04:41,788
Like they would say, So-and-so is with the security,
so-and-so is a former policeman, and so-and-so

63
00:04:41,813 --> 00:04:43,533
He has this item

64
00:04:43,558 --> 00:04:45,147
And this one has a weapon

65
00:04:45,508 --> 00:04:47,773
I mean, they would
inform on people
